# 🧩 Dual-License Summary (Non‑Legal Explanation)

This section does **not** modify the licenses.  
It only explains how the dual model works.

## ✔ You may choose MIT if you want:
- maximum freedom  
- minimal legal overhead  
- simple reuse in any project  

## ✔ You may choose Apache 2.0 if you want:
- patent protection  
- explicit contribution terms  
- enterprise‑grade legal clarity  

## ✔ Both licenses allow:
- commercial use  
- modification  
- distribution  
- private use  
- closed‑source integration  

